    <text>
        <body>
            <p>If there be a <sic>perserve</sic> man, who kept what is good away from many<lb/> Who
                twists that which is straight, and turns <sic>striaghtforwardness</sic><lb/> into
                rebellion<lb/> The dwellers of the world behold (in him) a wicked man and one who
                acts<lb/> with contrariness<lb/> A destroyer of the memory of the Faith, who lowers
                the cedar,<lb/> Oh ye who know the ways of the religion, please hear me,<lb/> He who
                reads his book will curse him, spit into his face.<lb/> His poetry is confused, and
                melts like snow.<lb/> He brings sacrifices to the desert spirits.<lb/> He calls out,
                “Let there be light”, about a book of emptiness and<lb/> vanity,<lb/> One who sees
                it laughs as at the wisdom of a mule.<lb/> And who told him all this that he
                did?<lb/> His folly is carved in deep.<lb/> The Creator of truth provides a healing
                for the disease.<lb/> He will repay with proper reward a man of sin and
                rebellion.<lb/> The unheeding will be lost, and we shall return to
                    <placeName>Zion</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The words of the truth-seeker and the one who desires<lb/>
                righteousness</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">Baruch Shelomo Levinthal</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName>Isaac<lb/> Goldstein</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">L</p>
        </body>
